"problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:157
#: ba8cd38b352e4b1786f79052db83ff19
msgid ""
"**Why is the GPU run sometimes *slower* than the CPU run?** The smoke-"
"test mesh is intentionally tiny (:math:`\\sim` 100 DOFs). At this scale, "
"the CUDA solve is dominated by one-time overheads — context creation, JIT"
" kernel compilation, host↔device transfers, and ``cuSPARSE``/``cuSOLVER``"
" workspace allocation — rather than by actual floating-point work. The "
"first GPU call also pays for CUDA driver initialization. Run a real-sized"
" problem (:math:`\\geq 10^4`–:math:`10^5` DOFs) to see the GPU pull "
"ahead; see :doc:`../performance/index` for benchmarks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:169
#: 74efa11f01f94316aed7425ab427cd4a
msgid ""
"**Which solver does ``A.solve(b)`` actually use by default?** "
"``SparseMatrix.solve`` is inherited from ``torch_sla.SparseTensor`` and "
"called with ``backend=\"auto\"``, ``method=\"auto\"``. torch-sla's auto-"
"selector then picks, based on device and problem size:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:174
#: 2887bed43a944651b66a1bd4222e12fa
msgid ""
"**CPU** → SciPy / **SuperLU** (``backend=\"scipy\"``, ``method=\"lu\"``) "
"— a direct factorization, fast and machine-precision for the sizes "
"reachable on CPU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:177
#: 538f6ee4a188478da0444184adda925c
msgid ""
"**CUDA, DOF < 2M** → **cuDSS** if available (``method=\"cholesky\"`` when"
" SPD, else ``ldlt`` / ``lu``); falls back to CuPy, and finally to the "
"PyTorch-native iterative CG."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:180
#: 302fdeb6819f4321b8aa6a8265c732d7
msgid ""
"**CUDA, DOF ≥ 2M** → PyTorch-native iterative solver "
"(``backend=\"pytorch\"``, ``method=\"cg\"`` for SPD or ``bicgstab`` "
"otherwise) with Jacobi preconditioning, to stay within GPU memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:185
#: d844caad794d495a8be694b96e49139a
msgid ""
"So the smoke test above runs **SuperLU on CPU** and **cuDSS Cholesky on "
"GPU** (Poisson is SPD), not an iterative solver. To pick a different "
"solver explicitly, pass ``backend=...`` / ``method=...`` to ``solve`` — "
"see :doc:`../user_guide/linear_solvers`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:190
#: 7dc41c3e7963400488886bc14848ddbb
msgid ""
"The optional backends marked ``--`` are *not* a failure: they simply "
"aren't installed. Pick the ones you need:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:193
#: b0fdbf9180c84e30a8c3bbdca4d45824
msgid ""
"**petsc** — distributed direct / iterative solvers, useful for very large"
" 3D problems on CPU clusters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:195
#: 48934e67f5bf4a4b8c7eeda8af2dc34c
msgid ""
"**cupy** / **cudss** — GPU sparse-direct solvers for fast factorization "
"of small-to-medium 3D problems on CUDA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:197
#: 8be5b64975704bccafcd98e61a5912b9
msgid ""
"**amg** — algebraic multigrid preconditioner; recommended for 3D "
"elasticity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/verify_install.rst:200
